body_html: @jhostetler According to the post here, there's a possible explanation. The file mapping name was randomly generated, however the names seem to be the same at the same time, causing the later one to be rejected due to the difference in size. It's very rare, for it is almost impossible to get the the same random 64-bit number in such a short time in a process.

body: @jhostetler According to the post [here](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/16027268/why-does-mapviewoffile-fail-with-error-access-denied), there's a possible explanation. The file mapping name was randomly generated, however the names seem to be the same at the same time, causing the later one to be rejected due to the difference in size. It's very rare, for it is almost impossible to get the the same random 64-bit number in such a short time in a process.
